        <p>Let's look at one more example.</p>

        <example>
            <statement>
                <p>Solve for <m>n</m> in <m>n-9+3n=n-3n</m>.</p>
            </statement>
            <solution>
                <p>To start solving this equation, we'll need to combine like terms. After this, we can put all terms containg <m>n</m> on one side of the equation and finish solving for <m>n</m>.
                    <md>
                        <mrow>n-9+3n\amp=n-3n</mrow>
                        <mrow>4n-9\amp=-2n</mrow>
                        <mrow>4n-9\highlight{{}-4n}\amp=-2n\highlight{{}-4n}</mrow>
                        <mrow>-9\amp=-6n</mrow>
                        <mrow>\frac{-9}{\highlight{-6}}\amp=\frac{-6n}{\highlight{-1}}</mrow>
                        <mrow>n\amp=\frac{3}{2}</mrow>
                    </md>
                </p>
                <p>Checking the solution is left as exercise.</p>
            </solution>       
        </example>
       
        <exercise>
            <statement>
                <p>Check the solution <m>\frac{3}{2}</m> in the equation <m>n-9+3n=n-3n</m>.</p>
            </statement>
            <solution>
                <p>
                    <md>
                        <mrow>n-9+3n\amp=n-3n</mrow>
                        <mrow>\frac{3}{2}-9+3\left(\frac{3}{2}\right)\amp\stackrel{?}{=}\frac{3}{2}-3\left(\frac{3}{2}\right)</mrow>
                        <mrow>\frac{3}{2}-9+\frac{9}{2}\amp\stackrel{?}{=}\frac{3}{2}-\frac{9}{2}</mrow>
                        <mrow>\frac{12}{2}-9\amp\stackrel{?}{=}-\frac{6}{2}</mrow>
                        <mrow>6-9\amp\stackrel{?}{=}-3</mrow>
                        <mrow>-3\amp\stackrel{?}{=}-3</mrow>
                    </md>
                </p>
            </solution>
        </exercise>
