        <example>
            <p>Virginia is designing a rectangular garden. The garden's length must be <m>4</m> meters less than three times the width, and its perimter must be <m>40</m> meters. Find the garden's legnth and width.</p>

            <p>Reminder: A rectangle's perimeter formula is <m>P=2(L+W)</m>, where <m>P</m> stands for perimeter, <m>L</m> stands for length and <m>W</m> stands for width.</p>

            <p>Assume the rectangle's width is <m>W</m> meters. We can then represent the length as <m>3W-4</m> meters since we are told that it is <m>4</m> meters less than three times the width. It's given that the perimeter is <m>40</m> meters. Substituting those values into the formula, we have:
                <md>
                    <mrow>P\amp=2(L+W)</mrow>
                    <mrow>40\amp=2(3W-4+W)</mrow>
                    <mrow>40\amp=2(4W-4)\amp\text{Like terms were combined.}</mrow>
                </md>
            </p>

            <p>The next step to solve this equation is to remove the parentheses by distribution. 
                <md>
                    <mrow>40\amp=2(4W-4)</mrow>
                    <mrow>40\amp=8W-8</mrow>
                    <mrow>40\highlight{{}+8}\amp=8W-8\highlight{{}+8}</mrow>
                    <mrow>48\amp=8W</mrow>
                    <mrow>6\amp=W</mrow>
                </md>
            </p>

            <p>To determine the length, recall that this was represented by <m>3W-4</m>, which is:
                <md>
                    <mrow>3W-4\amp=3(6)-4</mrow>
                    <mrow>\amp=14</mrow>
                 </md>
            </p> 
            
            <p>Thus the rectangle's width is <m>6</m> meters and the length is <m>14</m> meters. Checking this result is left as exercise.</p>
        </example>

        <exercise>
            <statement>
                <p>Check the solution <m>6</m> in the equation <m>40=2(4W-4)</m>.</p>
            </statement>
            <solution>
                <p>
                    <md>
                        <mrow>40\amp=2(4W-4)</mrow>
                        <mrow>40\amp\stackrel{?}{=}2(4(6)-4)</mrow>
                        <mrow>40\amp\stackrel{?}{=}2(20)</mrow>
                        <mrow>40\amp\stackrel{\checkmark}{=}40</mrow>
                    </md>
                </p>
            </solution>
        </exercise>


